com.dd.plist

Class NSDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dd.plist.NSObject
      • com.dd.plist.NSDictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,NSObject>

    public class NSDictionary
extends NSObject
implements Map<String,NSObject>
    The NSDictionary class is a collection of NSObject instances that are identified by strings. It represents a hash map where the keys are strings and the values NSObject instances. The implementation is based on a linked hash map, so that the order of the elements in the dictionary is preserved. You can access the keys through the function allKeys(). Access to the objects stored for each key is given through the function objectForKey(String key).
    Author:
    Daniel Dreibrodt
    See Also:
    Foundation NSDictionary documentation, LinkedHashMap
